<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF109-766-607  </DOCNO><DOCID>09 766 607.andO;</DOCID><JOURNAL>Modern Office Technology  Dec 1990 v35 n12 p15(2).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Control is key to off-site records storage.andM;</TITLE><TEXT><ABSTRACT>Companies are finding it necessary to retain a large percentage ofdocuments, facing problems with storing these records.andP;  Inactiverecords have begun to be stored off-site, due to limited spacewithin a company facility.andP;  Records managers need to beware of thedifferences between mini-warehouses and records managementfacilities in order to consider the advantages and disadvantagesof both.andP;  Mini-warehouses are used to store records that are notneeded on a daily basis, and often do not accommodate securityneeds, access to records, pest control or other environmentalissues.andP;  Records management facilities offer 24-hour perimetersecurity and alarm systems, requiring proper authorization beforedocuments can be removed.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Topic:     Data SecurityRecords ManagementComparisonBusiness PlanningSpace PlanningFacility management.andO;Feature:   illustrationphotograph.andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>